 713:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_spi.c ****     This subsection provides a set of functions allowing to manage the SPI
 714:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_spi.c ****     data transfers.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\LENOVO\AppData\Local\Temp\cc49NHMv.s 			page 14


 715:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 716:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_spi.c ****     [..] The SPI supports master and slave mode :
 717:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 718:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_spi.c ****     (#) There are two modes of transfer:
 719:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_spi.c ****        (++) Blocking mode: The communication is performed in polling mode.
 720:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_spi.c ****             The HAL status of all data processing is returned by the same function
 721:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_spi.c ****             after finishing transfer.
 722:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_spi.c ****        (++) No-Blocking mode: The communication is performed using Interrupts
 723:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_spi.c ****             or DMA, These APIs return the HAL status.
